TopicTitle: Crash on load... USI Tools the cause

Articles.Content:
After hours of loading the game continuously.  I've narrowed my issue down to USI Tools.  Normally I would remove the offending mod and go about my day, however, I really cant play without RoverDudes USI mods, and they all have the tools as a dependency (as far as I know).

 

The attached ksp.log is from a failed load that included all of the USI mods,  KSP-AVC, Texture Replacer Replaced and Enhanced Visual Environments.  Removing USITools allows me to load to the menu.

 

Edit:  I've come to realize the update 1.3.1 literally just released (I just came back to the game) and any mods with a dll will require a recompile.  Not happy that I wasted hours of time but... it is what it is.
